<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="602" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/1248: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-11T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 11,
                                        1922—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>169. Your telegram 114, October 12, 4 P.M.<note n="50" xml:id="d602fn50">Not printed; see despatch no. 6420, Oct. 12, from the Chargé in
                                Mexico, <ref target="#pg_700">p. 700</ref>.</note> and despatch
                            6520, October 26. If you see no objection you may say to Mr. Pani that
                            your Government has advised you that the draft petroleum bill submitted
                            with your despatch 6450, October 17,<note n="51" xml:id="d602fn51">Not
                                printed.</note> is entirely inadequate in the matter of the
                            protection of the lawfully acquired rights of American citizens.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>